    "Management": {
      "text": "Antibiotics not routinely given, but may be indicated for through and though lip lacerations\nConsider updating tetanus\nVermillion border and philtrum architecture must be maintained for cosmesis\nInfiltration of local anesthetic can distort soft tissue\nConsider\nNerve Block: Infraorbital\nfor upper lip,\nNerve Block: Mental\nfor lower lip\nConsider marking vermillion border prior to infiltration of anesthetic to facilitate repair",
      "subsections": {
        "Intraoral_mucosal_laceration_(isolated)": {
          "text": "Only need to close if >1cm\nUse absorbable 5-0 suture\nAvoid catching underlying muscle during suturing",
          "tables": []
        },
        "Through-and-through_laceration": {
          "text": "Close in layers:\nClose mucosal layer with absorbable 5-0 suture\nIrrigate from outside\nClose orbicularis oris muscle with 4-0 or 5-0 absorbable suture\nClose skin with 6-0 nonabsorbable suture",
          "tables": []
        },
        "Vermilion_border_laceration": {
          "text": "Place 1st stitch with 6-0 nonabsorbable suture to align edges of vermilion border\nThen repair rest of lip in usual manner",
          "tables": []
        }
      },
      "tables": [],
